'''Bauma''' is a [[railway station]] in the [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[canton of Zurich]] and [[Bauma|municipality of Bauma]]. The station is situated at the junction of the [[T<U+00F6>sstalbahn|T<U+00F6>sstal railway line]], which is still in full use, and the [[Uerikon<U+2013>Bauma railway|Uerikon to Bauma railway]] (UeBB), which is partly closed and partly used as a [[heritage railway]].<ref>{{cite map | publisher = Swiss Confederation | title = map.geo.admin.ch | url = http://map.geo.admin.ch/?selectedNode=node_ch.swisstopo.swissboundaries3d-gemeinde-flaeche.fill1&Y=708770&X=247540&zoom=8&bgLayer=ch.swisstopo.pixelkarte-farbe&layers=ch.swisstopo.swissboundaries3d-gemeinde-flaeche.fill&layers_opacity=1&layers_visibility=true&time_current=latest&lang=en | accessdate = 2013-04-03}}</ref><ref name=zvv>{{cite web | url = http://www.zvv.ch/export/sites/default/common-images/content-image-gallery/linien-zonen-pdfs/Liniennetzplan_ganzer_Verbund_2011.pdf | title = S-Bahn trains, buses and boats | publisher = ZVV | accessdate = 2012-03-08}}</ref><ref name=saw12-13>{{cite book | title = Eisenbahnatlas Schweiz | year = 2012 | publisher = Verlag Schweers + Wall GmbH | isbn=978-3-89494-130-7 | pages = 12-13}}</ref>

Bauma station is an intermediate station on the [[Zurich S-Bahn]] route [[S26 (ZVV)|S26]], which operates between [[Rapperswil]] and [[Winterthur]].<ref name=zvv/> 

Bauma station is also the terminus of services of the [[Dampfbahn-Verein Z<U+00FC>rcher Oberland]] (DVZO), who operate to [[Hinwil]], over the former UeBB, with trains normally hauled by [[steam locomotive]]s. The UeBB line beyond Hinwil, towards [[Uerikon]], was closed in 1948 and little now remains.<ref name=saw12-13/><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.dvzo.ch/index.php?N1_ID=184&N2_ID=173&N3_ID=105 | title = Fahrplan an den Fahrsonntagen im 2012 | trans_title = Sunday timetable for 2012 | language = German | publisher = DVZO | accessdate = 2012-03-08}}</ref>  

